# =============================================================================
# Vercel Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
# 
# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. This deployment uses same-origin API routes (/api/*).
# 2. For local development, the app defaults to http://localhost:3000/api.
# 3. For AI features, you MUST set OPENAI_API_KEY in Vercel Dashboard.
# 4. For persistent storage, you MUST set POSTGRES_URL in Vercel Dashboard.
#
# =============================================================================

# AI Configuration (Set these in Vercel Dashboard)
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# Database Configuration (Set this via Vercel Storage)
# POSTGRES_URL=postgres://...

# =============================================================================
# WARNING: DO NOT SET NEXT_PUBLIC_LIFEPATH_API_BASE_URL TO AN EXTERNAL URL!
# =============================================================================
#
# This app uses Vercel Serverless Functions for the backend API.
# All API calls should use same-origin routes (/api/*) which are served from
# the same Vercel deployment.
#
# If you previously deployed to Railway or another external backend:
#   1. Go to Vercel Dashboard → Project Settings → Environment Variables
#   2. DELETE the NEXT_PUBLIC_LIFEPATH_API_BASE_URL variable
#   3. Redeploy your application
#
# Setting this to an external URL (e.g., https://some-backend.railway.app)
# will cause API calls to fail because:
#   - NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables are embedded at BUILD TIME
#   - The external URL gets baked into the client bundle
#   - This causes CORS errors and broken API connections
#
# The correct configuration is to leave this UNSET (defaults to /api).
#
# =============================================================================

# API Configuration - Leave this commented out for Vercel deployments!
# Only uncomment if you explicitly need to override the default /api routes.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_LIFEPATH_API_BASE_URL=/api
